<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910219-0155</DOCNO><DOCID>910219-0155.</DOCID><HL>   Financing Business:   Hudson's Bay Co.</HL><DATE>02/19/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C19</SO><CO>   T.HBC</CO><IN>BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)BROADLINE RETAILERS, DEPARTMENT STORES (RTB)</IN><LP>   HUDSON'S BAY Co. (Toronto) -- This Toronto retailer saidit will offer to purchase all of its 3.6 million cumulativeredeemable preferred shares Series A at 20.75 Canadiandollars (US$18.) a share. The offer will be made through WoodGundy Inc. on the Toronto Stock Exchange between today andMarch 4. Any shares purchased by the retailer under the offerwill be cancelled. The company said it borrowed the fundsnecessary to make all required payments to the holders of theshares and intends to repay the loan from the proceeds of thesale of three million common shares. The company currentlyhas about 45.3 million common shares outstanding. A companyspokesman said the decision was made because preferred sharesare a costly source of financing.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>